confIfTable.name: confIfTable
confIfTable.description: The table contains configuration information for each IP link.

confIfEntry.name: confIfEntry
confIfEntry.description: Configuration information for the IP link.

confIfIndex.name: confIfIndex
confIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the IP link.

confIfAddrAndMask1.name: confIfAddrAndMask1
confIfAddrAndMask1.description: The primary IP Address and Mask of the IP link. The format of the octet string is: 4 bytes : IP Address. 4 bytes : Subnet Mask. A string of all zeros is used for unnumbered links.

confIfAddrAndMask2.name: confIfAddrAndMask2
confIfAddrAndMask2.description: The second IP Address and Mask of the IP link. The format of the octet string is: 4 bytes : IP Address. 4 bytes : Subnet Mask.

confIfAddrAndMask3.name: confIfAddrAndMask3
confIfAddrAndMask3.description: The third IP Address and Mask of the IP link. The format of the octet string is: 4 bytes : IP Address. 4 bytes : Subnet Mask.

confIfAddrAndMask4.name: confIfAddrAndMask4
confIfAddrAndMask4.description: The fourth IP Address and Mask of the IP link. The format of the octet string is: 4 bytes : IP Address. 4 bytes : Subnet Mask.

confIfRouteProto.name: confIfRouteProto
confIfRouteProto.description: The Routing Protocol used on the link.

confIfTrigRip.name: confIfTrigRip
confIfTrigRip.description: Indicates whether Triggered RIP is used on the link.

confIfRipMetric.name: confIfRipMetric
confIfRipMetric.description: The RIP metric used on the link.

confIfRip2AuthType.name: confIfRip2AuthType
confIfRip2AuthType.description: The RIP-2 Authentication type used on the link.

confIfRip2AuthKey.name: confIfRip2AuthKey
confIfRip2AuthKey.description: The authentication key used in RIP-2.

confIfBootpReqForw.name: confIfBootpReqForw
confIfBootpReqForw.description: Indicates whether BOOTP requests are forwarded on the link

confIfProxyArp.name: confIfProxyArp
confIfProxyArp.description: Indicates whether Proxy Arp is used on the link.

confIfFiltering.name: confIfFiltering
confIfFiltering.description: Indicates whether IP filtering is used on the link.

confIfRxDefAction.name: confIfRxDefAction
confIfRxDefAction.description: Indicates whether packets not matching any of the Rx filters on the link must be passed or discarded.

confIfTxDefAction.name: confIfTxDefAction
confIfTxDefAction.description: Indicates whether packets not matching any of the Tx filters on the link must be passed or discarded.

confIfRxDefLogging.name: confIfRxDefLogging
confIfRxDefLogging.description: Indicates whether packets not matching any of the Rx filters must be logged.

confIfTxDefLogging.name: confIfTxDefLogging
confIfTxDefLogging.description: Indicates whether packets not matching any of the Tx filters must be logged.

confIfCreateObj.name: confIfCreateObj
confIfCreateObj.description: Create a non existing table entry. If the entry already exist, genError is returned. Binary format: 4 bytes : confIfAddr1 4 bytes : confIfMask1 4 bytes : confIfAddr2 4 bytes : confIfMask2 4 bytes : confIfAddr3 4 bytes : confIfMask3 4 bytes : confIfAddr4 4 bytes : confIfMask4 1 byte : confIfRouteProto 1 byte : confIfTrigRip 1 byte : confIfRipMetric 1 byte : confIfRip2AuthType 16 bytes : confIfRip2AuthKey 1 byte : confIfBootpReqForw 1 byte : confIfProxyArp 1 byte : confIfFiltering 1 byte : confIfRxDefAction 1 byte : confIfTxDefAction 1 byte : confIfRxDefLogging 1 byte : confIfTxDefLogging 1 byte : confIfTtlThreshold 30 bytes : confIfTunnelName 4 bytes : confIfLocalIP 4 bytes : confIfRemoteIP 1 byte : confIfMgtAccess 1 byte : confIfRtrDiscovery

confIfMCRouteProto.name: confIfMCRouteProto
confIfMCRouteProto.description: The multicast Routing Protocol used on the link.

confIfDvmrpMetric.name: confIfDvmrpMetric
confIfDvmrpMetric.description: The DVMRP metric used on the link.

confIfTtlThreshold.name: confIfTtlThreshold
confIfTtlThreshold.description: The TTL Threshold used on the link.

confIfTunnelName.name: confIfTunnelName
confIfTunnelName.description: The symbolic name of the IP-in-IP tunnel.

confIfLocalIP.name: confIfLocalIP
confIfLocalIP.description: The Local IP address of the IP-in-IP tunnel.

confIfRemoteIP.name: confIfRemoteIP
confIfRemoteIP.description: The Remote IP address of the IP-in-IP tunnel.

confIfMgtAccess.name: confIfMgtAccess
confIfMgtAccess.description: Indicates whether management access to the router is allowed via the link.

confIfRtrDiscovery.name: confIfRtrDiscovery
confIfRtrDiscovery.description: Indicates whether the router is allowed to send ICMP Router Advertisement messages.

confIfType.name: confIfType
confIfType.description: Indicates the type of interface used for the link.

confMgtAddress.name: confMgtAddress
confMgtAddress.description: Enabled if the first address of this interface is the management address.

filterTable.name: filterTable
filterTable.description: The table contains IP filter configuration information.

filterEntry.name: filterEntry
filterEntry.description: Configuration information for the IP filter.

filterIfIndex.name: filterIfIndex
filterIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the IP link on which the filter is used.

filterDirIndex.name: filterDirIndex
filterDirIndex.description: Indicates whether the filter is an Rx or Tx filter.

filterIndex.name: filterIndex
filterIndex.description: Index in the Rx or Tx filter list for the link.

filterAction.name: filterAction
filterAction.description: The action to be taken when a packet matches the filter. Disabled filters are ignored.

filterLogging.name: filterLogging
filterLogging.description: Indicates whether packets matching the filter must be logged.

filterProtocol.name: filterProtocol
filterProtocol.description: Indicates whether the filter matches all protocols, a user defined protocol or a known protocol.

filterProtocolValue.name: filterProtocolValue
filterProtocolValue.description: The protocol field in the IP header of the packet.

filterTcpFlags.name: filterTcpFlags
filterTcpFlags.description: Indicates whether the filter matches all TCP packets or only TCP packets with the ACK flag set. When the ACK flag is set, the packet belongs to an established TCP connection.

filterSrcAddrType.name: filterSrcAddrType
filterSrcAddrType.description: Indicates whether the filter matches all source addresses, addresses on a specific network or a specific host address.

filterSrcAddr.name: filterSrcAddr
filterSrcAddr.description: Indicates the network or host address which the source address must match.

filterSrcMask.name: filterSrcMask
filterSrcMask.description: The subnet mask of the network which the source address must match.

filterSrcPort.name: filterSrcPort
filterSrcPort.description: Indicates whether the filter matches all or a specific UDP/TCP source port.

filterSrcPortValue.name: filterSrcPortValue
filterSrcPortValue.description: The UDP/TCP source port of the filter.

filterSrcPortOper.name: filterSrcPortOper
filterSrcPortOper.description: The source port operator indicates whether UDP/TCP source port values equal to, not equal to, greater than or less than the filter source port match the filter.

filterDestAddrType.name: filterDestAddrType
filterDestAddrType.description: Indicates whether the filter matches all destination addresses, addresses on a specific network or a specific host address.

filterDestAddr.name: filterDestAddr
filterDestAddr.description: Indicates the network or host address which the destination address must match.

filterDestMask.name: filterDestMask
filterDestMask.description: The subnet mask of the network which the destination address must match.

filterDestPort.name: filterDestPort
filterDestPort.description: Indicates whether the filter matches all or a specific UDP/TCP destination port.

filterDestPortValue.name: filterDestPortValue
filterDestPortValue.description: The UDP/TCP destination port of the filter.

filterDestPortOper.name: filterDestPortOper
filterDestPortOper.description: The destination port operator indicates whether UDP/TCP destination port values equal to, not equal to, greater than or less than the filter destination port match the filter.

filterHits.name: filterHits
filterHits.description: The number of packets matching the filter.

natIfIndex.name: natIfIndex
natIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the IP link on which the NAT entry is used.

natIntAddr.name: natIntAddr
natIntAddr.description: The Internal IP Address of the NAT entry.

natIntMask.name: natIntMask
natIntMask.description: The Internal Mask of the NAT entry.

natIntPort.name: natIntPort
natIntPort.description: The Internal Port of the NAT entry.

natExtAddr.name: natExtAddr
natExtAddr.description: The External IP Address of the NAT entry.

natExtMask.name: natExtMask
natExtMask.description: The External Mask of the NAT entry.

natExtPort.name: natExtPort
natExtPort.description: The External Port of the NAT entry.

natType.name: natType
natType.description: Indicates whether the NAT entry is static or dynamic.

natTime.name: natTime
natTime.description: The time left for dynamic NAT entries.

statRoutTable.name: statRoutTable
statRoutTable.description: The table contains static route information.

statRoutEntry.name: statRoutEntry
statRoutEntry.description: Information for the static route entry.

statRoutIfIndex.name: statRoutIfIndex
statRoutIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the IP link on which the static route is used.

statRoutCreateObj.name: statRoutCreateObj
statRoutCreateObj.description: Create a non existing table entry. If the entry already exist, genError is returned. Binary format: 4 bytes : statRoutMask 4 bytes : statRoutNextHop 4 bytes : statRoutMetric

tosPrefThreshold.name: tosPrefThreshold
tosPrefThreshold.description: The threshold for Type of Service for the IP router. IP packets have a Precendence value in the Type of Service field. If the value is higher than the threshold the packet will be forwarded with high priority.

statIfTable.name: statIfTable
statIfTable.description: The table contains statistic information for each IP link.

statIfEntry.name: statIfEntry
statIfEntry.description: Statistic information for the IP link.

statIfIndex.name: statIfIndex
statIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the IP link.

statIfType.name: statIfType
statIfType.description: The type of the network (LAN or WAN) to which the IP link is connected.

statIfState.name: statIfState
statIfState.description: The actual state of the IP link. The link layer informs the IP link of link state changes.

statIfMTU.name: statIfMTU
statIfMTU.description: The maximum transmit unit of the IP link. IP packets larger than the MTU will be fragmented.

statIfRxDefHits.name: statIfRxDefHits
statIfRxDefHits.description: The number of packets that did not match any of the Rx Filters for the link.

statIfTxDefHits.name: statIfTxDefHits
statIfTxDefHits.description: The number of packets that did not match any of the Tx Filters for the link.

statIfChange.name: statIfChange
statIfChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time any IP link changed state.

ipIfIndex.name: ipIfIndex
ipIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the IP link.

ipIfInReceives.name: ipIfInReceives
ipIfInReceives.description: The number of IP packets received on the link.

ipIfInHdrErrors.name: ipIfInHdrErrors
ipIfInHdrErrors.description: The number of IP packets received on the link which were discarded because of IP header errors.

ipIfInAddrErrors.name: ipIfInAddrErrors
ipIfInAddrErrors.description: The number of IP packets received on the link which were discarded because of IP source or destination address errors.

ipIfInDiscards.name: ipIfInDiscards

ipIfOutDiscards.name: ipIfOutDiscards
ipIfOutDiscards.description: The number of IP packets which should have been sent on the link, but were discarded because of lack of buffer space or failed ARP requests.

icmpIfInMsgs.description: The number of ICMP messages to the router received on the link.

icmpIfInErrors.name: icmpIfInErrors
icmpIfInErrors.description: The number of ICMP messages to the router received on the link which were discarded because of ICMP header errors.

icmpInRouterAdvs.name: icmpInRouterAdvs
icmpInRouterAdvs.description: The total number of received ICMP Router Advertisements.

icmpInRouterSols.name: icmpInRouterSols
icmpInRouterSols.description: The total number of received ICMP Router Solicitations.

icmpOutRouterAdvs.description: The total number of sent ICMP Router Advertisements.

icmpOutRouterSols.name: icmpOutRouterSols

ripIfTable.name: ripIfTable
ripIfTable.description: The table contains RIP information for each IP link.

ripIfEntry.name: ripIfEntry
ripIfEntry.description: RIP information for the IP link.

ripIfIndex.name: ripIfIndex
ripIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the IP link.

ripIfInReceives.name: ripIfInReceives
ripIfInReceives.description: The number of RIP packets received on the link.

ripIfInHdrErrors.name: ripIfInHdrErrors
ripIfInHdrErrors.description: The number of RIP packets received on the link which were discarded because of RIP header errors.

ripIfInBadSrcAddrs.name: ripIfInBadSrcAddrs
ripIfInBadSrcAddrs.description: The number of RIP packets received on the link which were discarded because of source address errors. This may indicate an IP address configuration error on the link or the link of the router from which the RIP packet was received. The error may also occur if the link is connected to a physical network with multiple logical IP networks. In the latter case a source address error is not an indication of an IP address configuration error.

ripIfInBadVers.name: ripIfInBadVers
ripIfInBadVers.description: The number of RIP packets received on the link which were discarded because of RIP version errors. This indicates a RIP configuration error on the link or the link of the router from which the RIP packet was received. The error occurs when receiving a RIP packet with a version different from the version configured on the link. The error also occurs if a RIP packet is received and the link is configured not to use RIP.

ripIfInAuthFails.name: ripIfInAuthFails
ripIfInAuthFails.description: The number of RIP packets received on the link which were discarded because of RIP-2 authentication failures.

ripIfInUnknComs.name: ripIfInUnknComs
ripIfInUnknComs.description: The number of RIP packets received on the link which were discarded because of an unknown command type. This may indicate that the link is not configured to use Triggered RIP and the remote router is using Triggered RIP.

ripIfOutSent.name: ripIfOutSent
ripIfOutSent.description: The number of RIP packets sent on the link.

ripIfOutDiscards.name: ripIfOutDiscards
ripIfOutDiscards.description: The number of RIP packets discarded because of lack of buffer space.

ripInReceives.name: ripInReceives
ripInReceives.description: The total number of received RIP packets.

ripInHdrErrors.name: ripInHdrErrors
ripInHdrErrors.description: The total number of received RIP packets discarded because of RIP header errors.

ripInBadSrcAddrs.name: ripInBadSrcAddrs
ripInBadSrcAddrs.description: The total number of received RIP packets discarded because of source address errors.

ripInBadVers.name: ripInBadVers
ripInBadVers.description: The total number of received RIP packets discarded because of RIP version errors.

ripInAuthFails.name: ripInAuthFails
ripInAuthFails.description: The total number of RIP-2 authentication failures.

ripInUnknComs.name: ripInUnknComs
ripInUnknComs.description: The total number of received RIP packets discarded because of an unknown command type.

ripOutSent.name: ripOutSent
ripOutSent.description: The total number of RIP packets sent by the router.

ripOutDiscards.name: ripOutDiscards
ripOutDiscards.description: The total number of RIP packets discarded because of lack of buffer space.

bootpIfEntry.description: BOOTP information for the IP link.

bootpIfInErrors.name: bootpIfInErrors
bootpIfInErrors.description: The number of BOOTP packets received on the link which were discarded because of header errors.

bootpIfInDiscards.name: bootpIfInDiscards
bootpIfInDiscards.description: The number of BOOTP requests received on the link which were discarded. This is done in the following situations: - The maximum value of the BOOTP hop count is exceeded. - More than 3 BOOTP packets are received per second. - The router does not have a route back to the assisting router using the receving link.

bootpIfOutReplies.description: The number of BOOTP replies sent on the link.

bootpIfOutDiscards.description: The number of BOOTP requests discarded because of lack of buffer space.

bootpInRequests.description: The total number of received BOOTP requests.

bootpInReplies.name: bootpInReplies
bootpInReplies.description: The total number of received BOOTP replies.

bootpInErrors.name: bootpInErrors
bootpInErrors.description: The total number of received BOOTP packets discarded because of header errors.

bootpInDiscards.name: bootpInDiscards
bootpInDiscards.description: The total number of received BOOTP requests discarded. This is done in the following situations: - The maximum value of the BOOTP hop count is exceeded. - More than 3 BOOTP packets are received per second. - The router does not have a route back to the assisting router using the receiving link.

bootpOutRequests.description: The total number of BOOTP requests sent by the router.

bootpOutReplies.description: The total number of BOOTP replies sent to BOOTP clients.

bootpOutDiscards.description: The total number of BOOTP requests discarded because of lack of buffer space.

bootpMaxHops.name: bootpMaxHops
bootpMaxHops.description: The maximum allowed value of the hop count in received BOOTP requests.
